Interface IExtractionQueue

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    CommitQueue

    public interface IExtractionQueue
    This interface declares the methods a CommitQueue has to implement for its use by a commit extractor.
    Author:
    Christian Kroeher

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      boolean addCommit(Commit commit)
      Adds the given Commit to the end of this queue if its status is CommitQueue.QueueState.OPEN and the queue is not full.

    • Method Detail

      • addCommit

        boolean addCommit(Commit commit)
        Adds the given Commit to the end of this queue if its status is CommitQueue.QueueState.OPEN and the queue is not full.
        Parameters:
        commit - the new commit added to the end of this queue if the queue is open
        Returns:
        true if adding the commit to this queue was successful; false if the queue has not the status CommitQueue.QueueState.OPEN or there are currently too much commits in the queue
